I could see a major war. I could see a major event coming. That was the biggest storm.

00:29:00.409 --> 00:29:10.839
I could see it on the East Coast. This storm was so ginormous. It was a massive storm.

00:29:10.840 --> 00:29:21.839
As this storm was trying to overshadow our president, I saw a darkness trying to come upon him.

00:29:21.840 --> 00:29:37.918
That was an Antichrist anointing, trying to influence his mind, trying to influence him with great pressure.

00:29:37.919 --> 00:29:45.439
He was resisting, but it was the pressure of the end times. It was the pressure of where we are.

00:29:45.440 --> 00:29:57.319
There is such a pull for the end of the end, for this dispensation of grace is coming to an end.

00:29:57.320 --> 00:30:02.926
Tribulation is about to begin. And the birthing pains are all around us. We've talked about that.

00:30:02.927 --> 00:30:12.959
But the pressure of where we are is felt on even the greatest leader, the leader of the free world.

00:30:12.960 --> 00:30:19.525
And I saw a darkness that looked like a cloak that was in the background trying to influence him.

00:30:19.526 --> 00:30:28.340
And the Lord said, 'Do you see the reason why I'm calling everyone to pray? To intercede for his mind?

00:30:28.341 --> 00:30:45.919
To intercede for him all the time so that he does not get—'If it was anybody else like an Obama or anybody, it tries to engulf you, but you have to submit yourself therefore unto God, resist the devil and he will flee.

00:30:45.920 --> 00:30:52.319
Regardless of temptation or whatever, all of us have to do it. That's what the Bible commissioned and told us to do.

00:30:52.320 --> 00:31:00.620
But even him with the greatest position, the leading of all this, this pressure of the end times... it was pressure.

00:31:00.621 --> 00:31:13.839
It looked like someone had put on this black whatever this was, it looked like something that would weigh thousands of pounds on top of his shoulders.

00:31:13.840 --> 00:31:20.999
And I was looking at it and he was in the Oval Office and it was trying to change his countenance.

00:31:21.000 --> 00:31:33.396
It was trying to change his thinking because it is a spirit. It's the same kind of demonic spirit that tried to mess with Hitler, but Hitler yielded to it.

00:31:33.397 --> 00:31:48.079
It's the difference between somebody saying, 'I'm tempted to do whatever.'You can either resist it, or you can succumb to the temptation.

00:31:48.080 --> 00:31:55.839
Everyone's human. Do you understand? And nobody knows the pressure of leading the United States of America.

00:31:55.840 --> 00:32:09.199
Nobody does it unless you're a president. And I saw the pressure of the position, but it wasn't just about leading the Western world or America.

00:32:09.200 --> 00:32:26.387
It was about what was influencing the end-time events concerning digital currency, the First Amendment, the Second Amendment, our Bill of Rights, and everything.

00:32:26.388 --> 00:32:36.279
It was pressure because it's Agenda 2030. It's concerning taking away freedoms from people. Do you understand?

00:32:36.280 --> 00:32:57.225
As I was seeing that Illuminati wall with the mask and the demonic cow that was demanding blood sacrifice of children, we see the pressure of everything.

00:32:57.226 --> 00:33:14.496
When I was looking at it, I could see the end times. But then I saw one behind him and I could see dates and I could see somebody that is a chameleon.

00:33:14.497 --> 00:33:21.639
As I was looking into this, it kind of freaked me out, and that's why I never use some of these names that I see.

00:33:21.640 --> 00:33:52.851
But I saw—I won't call it a betrayal; I'll call it a yielding to it. Some people have character and some people don't.

00:33:52.852 --> 00:34:07.159
Whenever you're thrust into great responsibility when you have not been on the potter's wheel of refining, your character can't handle something that is put on you so quickly.

00:34:07.160 --> 00:34:15.678
That's like if you gave someone who is 19 years old a billion dollars and they were never raised with money.

00:34:15.679 --> 00:34:28.639
If they were never raised in a household that had money like that and you gave a 19-year-old that kind of money, what would it do to them?

00:34:28.640 --> 00:34:33.559
It would destroy them because they don't have the character to handle it.

00:34:33.560 --> 00:34:39.878
So, I saw great responsibility come upon people that weren't ready for it.

00:34:39.879 --> 00:35:03.839
And as the pressure of something so big—and it wasn't just about America, it was about the end times—President Trump is almost 80; his birthday is coming in May, so he's seasoned.

00:35:03.840 --> 00:35:17.206
And he's even struggling. You can tell with all this pressure, it's something that most of us could never even hold.

00:35:17.207 --> 00:35:36.759
That's why I'm trying to tell you all what I saw. I saw Europe. I saw certain leaders and I saw great war and the plague.

00:35:36.760 --> 00:35:40.161
I could see another plague; I could see a major shaking of the plague.

00:35:40.162 --> 00:35:46.479
But at the same time, I could see the church and I could see people running to church.

00:35:46.480 --> 00:35:57.599
And the glory was there. The glorious church was rising and it was something to be seen.

00:35:57.600 --> 00:36:10.079
I try to focus more on the glorious side. Like I said, it's that thin of a line. It's rice-paper thin.

00:36:10.080 --> 00:36:18.317
It's even thinner than that, of how close the glory will be and the darkness. It's like a quarter.

00:36:18.318 --> 00:36:27.402
And there's so many people that don't realize how hard of times there will be for some people. He said, 'I've warned and I've warned.

00:36:27.403 --> 00:36:34.999
I've yelled and I've yelled to warn the people of that which is to come, and they haven't had ears to hear.

00:36:35.000 --> 00:36:48.498
They haven't prepared. Many of you will be caught off guard. Many of you will make it. I saw that a lot of you would make it.

00:36:48.499 --> 00:36:56.959
But it's the difference between making it and being in abundance, and making it and being in survival mode.

00:36:56.960 --> 00:37:08.919
Both make it; one's just more comfortable than the other. God will always take care of His kids; God will always provide for His kids.

00:37:08.920 --> 00:37:28.439
But there's a difference between just eating and having the good of the land. Does that make sense? Just because you listen to Him.

00:37:28.440 --> 00:37:39.055
Joseph had plenty, but his brothers were lacking and they had to ask him for help.

00:37:39.056 --> 00:37:54.239
Joseph's like, 'Well, if you would have been with me, I would have told you how to get everything ready for the last seven years, and you weren't ready, but great famine's coming.'Joseph knew and he was ready, but his brothers were still taken care of.

00:37:54.240 --> 00:37:59.382
They still got everything, but they had to come to themselves in that hard time.

00:37:59.383 --> 00:38:05.759
They went to him to ask for help in the drought and the famine.

00:38:05.760 --> 00:38:12.907
Maybe that's not a good illustration for what I've seen, but it's something that the people need to understand.

00:38:12.908 --> 00:38:19.399
We've never experienced what we're about to experience, especially in this generation.

00:38:19.400 --> 00:38:31.293
There's many of you that are so used to going through McDonald's and having it your way that you've never seen some of the things that I have seen in the spirit.

00:38:31.294 --> 00:38:40.740
I've never experienced it, but what I see is not really pleasant to my flesh.

00:38:40.741 --> 00:38:49.254
I always go, 'Tell me the rapture of the church happens before some of this.'That's why I get quiet.

00:38:49.255 --> 00:38:59.186
Are we really here for that? The church was here. I could see it. It didn't look that great to me.

00:38:59.187 --> 00:39:05.934
The church was walking in glory and we were laying hands on people and there was blessing on the people.

00:39:05.935 --> 00:39:20.366
Do you remember whenever I said Deuteronomy 6:11? Yeah, there will be vineyards you do not plant.

00:39:20.367 --> 00:39:24.556
Houses filled with all kinds of good things you did not provide.

00:39:24.557 --> 00:39:30.438
Wells you did not dig and vineyards and olive groves you did not plant.

00:39:30.439 --> 00:39:55.439
Then when you eat and are satisfied, he said there'll be a remnant of you, a one percent, that this wealth transfer is going to be such a blessing that you're going to be able to help the other people out because you listened and obeyed.

00:39:55.440 --> 00:40:03.228
And there will be a wealth transfer for houses filled with all kinds of good things you did not provide.

00:40:03.229 --> 00:40:06.919
That means you didn't have to work for it. It's just there. God did it.

00:40:06.920 --> 00:40:13.439
Wells you did not dig. It took a long time to dig a well back then and get a good one.

00:40:13.440 --> 00:40:18.839
Vineyards—a lot of work. And olive groves you did not plant.

00:40:18.840 --> 00:40:23.128
You just got it because the wealth of the sinner is laid up for the righteous.

00:40:23.129 --> 00:40:26.657
That's what He was showing me last night. And that was concerning certain ministers.

00:40:26.658 --> 00:40:33.839
I even brought up John Kilpatrick. I saw great blessing coming on this man and his church.

00:40:33.840 --> 00:40:43.466
I saw certain key members in his church last night that had invested and they're about to come into a lot of money.

00:40:43.467 --> 00:40:50.639
When I was in the spirit, I could see this man's church. I am not affiliated with him at all.

00:40:50.640 --> 00:40:58.159
I don't know him. I don't even watch them. I've watched a couple of his sermons, but the Lord brings it up to me.

00:40:58.160 --> 00:41:12.719
I see his face, but there's something about him that the Lord tells me, 'Pray for this man, for his health, specifically for him to be strong, because God has a plan for his life.'But He said this to me about this man.

00:41:12.720 --> 00:41:20.759
He gave me Deuteronomy for him. And that was concerning his church.

00:41:20.760 --> 00:41:28.639
And the Lord said, 'Lay hold to it.'He said, 'There's many of you that have not been obedient to doing what He's asking you to do.

00:41:28.640 --> 00:41:34.559
You've pushed it away. You have a call on your life and you've not yielded to it.

00:41:34.560 --> 00:41:40.639
You've not been obedient to what God's called you to do. It's all hands on deck right now.

00:41:40.640 --> 00:41:52.319
For the harvest is plentiful and the laborers are few. Will you obey what God has called you to do in these last days and stop running from Him?

00:41:52.320 --> 00:41:59.519
He's going to bypass you and go to the next person if you keep putting up your hands and say He's out of time.

00:41:59.520 --> 00:42:12.799
He's not begging you. 'You? You're only 15. I don't care. Come on.

00:42:12.800 --> 00:42:21.039
How old are you? You're 12. Let's do it.'Nothing's going to disqualify you.

00:42:21.040 --> 00:42:25.838
Keep underneath the mighty hand of the Lord and humble yourself. Keep out of sin.

00:42:25.839 --> 00:42:30.639
Keep yourself right before Him by prayer and fasting, seeking Him daily.

00:42:30.640 --> 00:42:37.654
Now, if you fall down in sin, you run to God when you sin; you don't run away from Him. I'm not saying that any of us are perfect.

00:42:37.655 --> 00:42:45.279
But I'm not saying you deliberately practice and do things that you know you shouldn't be doing.

00:42:45.280 --> 00:42:52.079
Now, if you mess up in life and you drop a bad word or something, people mess up.

00:42:52.080 --> 00:42:55.438
I'm talking about people who are deliberately... you know what, bud?

00:42:55.439 --> 00:43:01.559
Let's go to the strip club this weekend and we'll repent on Sunday.

00:43:01.560 --> 00:43:08.656
Let's go out and get drunk tonight. Let's go get wasted. You know that's wrong, but you do it because, you know what?

00:43:08.657 --> 00:43:19.568
It's okay; God knows it's under grace. You know, it's okay to cheat on your wife or husband or whatever; I'll repent about it.

00:43:19.569 --> 00:43:23.239
She's not fulfilling my needs. He's not fulfilling my needs.

00:43:23.240 --> 00:43:30.959
So, I'm just going to go out and, you know, we have an open marriage; it's cool.

00:43:30.960 --> 00:43:40.333
It's wrong, and you know it's wrong, but yet you keep dipping in.

00:43:40.334 --> 00:43:46.159
The wages of sin is death, and that's what I'm talking about.

00:43:46.160 --> 00:43:50.040
You know it's wrong, and you keep trying. You keep doing the same thing over.

00:43:50.041 --> 00:44:02.801
You don't run to God; you run to the devil and his crowd and think, 'Well, I'm saved by grace. I can live both sides.

00:44:02.802 --> 00:44:11.239
One foot is over here and I have one foot over there, and we're okay.'And those are the ones I'm talking about right now. It's time to be all in.

00:44:11.240 --> 00:44:24.679
It's time to sell out for Jesus, to look at Him as a holy God, and we are made in His image and we need to be holy as He is holy.

00:44:24.680 --> 00:44:31.919
I'm going to do everything I can to be as far away from the world and what they want and what they think is cool.

00:44:31.920 --> 00:44:40.513
I want to be as close as I can to Him, sitting in His lap, listening to His breath. What can I do to be closer to Him?

00:44:40.514 --> 00:44:55.183
I'm not just right on the edge of living in the world and barely in the church; I want to be all in. I want to know what His breath smells like if He has breath.

00:44:55.184 --> 00:45:04.079
If He has bad breath that day, which I'm sure He doesn't, but if He did, I want to know that He did, or what kind of fragrance He had.

00:45:04.080 --> 00:45:09.919
'Did you spray some cologne on, Lord? I want to know what You have on today.

00:45:09.920 --> 00:45:22.639
What is it? Is it frankincense today?'I want that because I'm that close. I just want to know Him.

00:45:22.640 --> 00:45:30.439
And I know that when you seek Him, you will find Him because I have those moments like I had last night.

00:45:30.440 --> 00:45:36.112
And I could see all that was coming. And after it was over, the presence filled me.

00:45:36.113 --> 00:45:45.759
I could feel it all day today quietly. I learned to get quieter as I talked to my friend Billy Burke.

00:45:45.760 --> 00:45:53.519
He's not a chatterbox. He stays to himself, and you learn from people who walk with Him.

00:45:53.520 --> 00:46:02.439
What does it take? And what does God say about you whenever I get off the phone with you?

00:46:02.440 --> 00:46:17.119
Not that I'm perfect, but it's always a fragrance. What is the fragrance that you leave in His nostrils? Does He call you friend?

00:46:17.120 --> 00:46:28.693
I love it whenever the Lord says to me, 'Billy's my friend.'Walk carefully when you talk that way to Him.

00:46:28.694 --> 00:46:42.830
'He's my friend.'It challenges me. I go, 'He's Your friend.'Honor Him when you're on the phone.

00:46:42.831 --> 00:46:46.099
Say this. Don't say that. Don't ever say that. Don't disrespect Him.

00:46:46.100 --> 00:46:49.768
He corrects me about certain things, and I'm just a young guy.

00:46:49.769 --> 00:46:54.096
Some things, like I said earlier, just dumb things sometimes come out of your mouth when you chatter.

00:46:54.097 --> 00:47:17.239
You talk to somebody that's older and the Lord says, 'Hush.'What does the Father think about you? What is the fragrance that you leave around Him?

00:47:17.240 --> 00:47:34.276
I want so badly for Him to want to visit my house and feel comfortable here, where He says, 'You know what? I can go there and I know I won't be grieved.

00:47:34.278 --> 00:47:45.519
Take not Thy Spirit from me.'Kathryn Kuhlman used to say things like that, and I thought she sounded kind of nutty because I was ignorant.

00:47:45.520 --> 00:47:58.106
But the older I get and the more I spend at His feet, I realize there is—like I said, I can feel it when He withdraws like that when I said that about the redhead thing.

00:47:58.108 --> 00:48:07.919
I went, 'Oh, I grieved it. It's not right.'Repent. Be sensitive.

00:48:07.920 --> 00:48:15.199
And the more you spend time with Him, your words are heavy and they have a lot of weight.

00:48:15.200 --> 00:48:25.559
And you'll learn you just can't flap your mouth all the time, especially having Him around.

00:48:25.560 --> 00:48:30.694
He has an opinion about everything. The Lord has an opinion about everything.

00:48:30.695 --> 00:48:39.692
And He says, 'Think on these things: whatsoever things are lovely, whatsoever things are pure, whatsoever things are of good report.'I could go on and on.

00:48:39.693 --> 00:48:51.079
In 1 Corinthians 13, love takes no account of a suffered wrong. I don't know how many times He corrects me about love.

00:48:51.080 --> 00:49:02.520
But faith works by love, and God is love, and the greater part of the anointing is walking in love. The angels visited.

00:49:02.521 --> 00:49:18.636
I remember I told you they said that he doesn't realize that most of what he gets before the Father, he'll be judged upon—what he's judged upon the most—is: how did he walk in love?

00:49:18.637 --> 00:49:26.799
How did he treat his fellow brethren? How did he walk in love?

00:49:26.800 --> 00:49:35.399
How did you treat people when you think you're better than them? Do you bless them?

00:49:35.400 --> 00:49:45.319
Do you help the waiter out at the table that's serving you, and they may have had a rough day?

00:49:45.320 --> 00:49:50.679
Do you treat them with honor and give them a good tip, or do you just give a little bit?

00:49:50.680 --> 00:49:58.479
'Here's a buck.'What are you going to do with a dollar? She has to feed her family.

00:49:58.480 --> 00:50:11.399
If you can't afford to give a tip, don't go out to eat then. I say go through the drive-thru, but don't treat people bad.

00:50:11.400 --> 00:50:19.329
I always try to walk in love. I'm not always saying that I've been good at that, but the Lord rebukes me about certain things now.

00:50:19.330 --> 00:50:30.282
And He'll say, 'Brandon, that's a poverty mentality. What you're doing and how you just acted right then is poverty.'I say, 'Break poverty.'It's a mindset.

00:50:30.283 --> 00:50:51.759
It's a stronghold. Break poverty off of your life by how you think and how you act, how you sow, what you're believing, what you're saying.

00:50:51.760 --> 00:51:11.439
So when I saw it last night and I saw all that, I was bothered—not because of what I saw, but because there are so many of you that have no idea what's coming and you're not ready.

00:51:11.440 --> 00:51:19.639
And I've tried so hard to convey to you: it's time for you to learn how to believe God for five dollars.

00:51:19.640 --> 00:51:37.559
It's time for you to believe—what if there was no way for you to go get a surgery and you really needed it? Can you believe God for a toenail that hurts?

00:51:37.560 --> 00:51:52.599
When it comes down to it and we're in the end times and we see these things around us, could I believe for the impossible—the surgery—that God would come through?

00:51:52.600 --> 00:52:01.279
I saw people around tables that had nothing, and they would hold their hands.

00:52:01.280 --> 00:52:10.346
I saw pots of food fill up with beans and cornbread and potatoes.

00:52:10.347 --> 00:52:20.839
I saw families that had steaming pots of food within just seconds when they gave grace. God showed up and did a miracle.

00:52:20.840 --> 00:52:33.759
Now, I've heard of other people having the same kind of visions, but the Lord warned me and He said, 'Brandon, the Bible says I've never seen the righteous forsaken or a seed begging bread.

00:52:33.760 --> 00:52:40.506
Either you believe it or you don't.'George Mueller was one of them. He had the orphanages and all this.

00:52:40.508 --> 00:52:51.945
He would start out believing for five dollars, and then he said it was just as easy to believe for five dollars as it was for a million later on in his walk with the Lord.

00:52:51.946 --> 00:52:58.359
So he could believe for a million dollars or he could believe for five dollars, but it was the same amount of faith after a while.

00:52:58.360 --> 00:53:07.359
He built himself up to it. So a million dollars wasn't much for him anymore, just like five bucks.

00:53:07.360 --> 00:53:15.079
But it took faith and patience. Faith works. Work it. Faith without works is dead.

00:53:15.080 --> 00:53:21.039
So, all right, I've talked too much again tonight, but I've tried to warn you all.

00:53:21.040 --> 00:53:28.079
You better start activating your faith. Believe God for the impossible.

00:53:28.080 --> 00:53:34.070
Get in the Word. Faith cometh by hearing and hearing by the Word of God. That's the only way faith comes.

00:53:34.071 --> 00:53:50.879
'Well, I bet if I had visitations from Jesus, if I had visitations from angels and all the things that you say you've had, Brandon, I bet I'd have great faith.'No, it had nothing to do with it.

00:53:50.880 --> 00:53:57.185
Because the moment you have challenges, you doubt those things and it comes up in your heart.

00:53:57.186 --> 00:54:00.358
The only thing that ever keeps me anchored is the word of God.

00:54:00.359 --> 00:54:09.126
Faith comes by hearing, and hearing by the word of God—not an experience. I don't care what kind of great experience you've had.

00:54:09.127 --> 00:54:16.802
If you don't have the word of God down inside of your heart, whenever the storms of life come, the experience never will keep you.

00:54:16.803 --> 00:54:33.523
The word will. And I've seen Jesus nine times now. He visits and I'll talk to him, and I don't say that to brag.

00:54:33.524 --> 00:54:44.759
It's more than that now. Because he stood here—he came to the house twice.

00:54:44.760 --> 00:54:50.451
So over the course of my life now, it's going on a lot. Why, Brandon?

00:54:50.452 --> 00:54:57.759
Why you? I don't know. He'll visit any one of you if you seek him.

00:54:57.760 --> 00:55:03.443
I'm just thankful when he does. How many angels? This is the thing I never tell you.

00:55:03.444 --> 00:55:17.639
You know how many times I see demons? More than I see the other, but I never talk about it. In fact, I saw three today, but I don't talk about it.

00:55:17.640 --> 00:55:26.905
Why give glory to something that's fallen and has already been defeated with your words? Why give them power in your words?

00:55:26.906 --> 00:55:32.756
The more you exalt them—they're exalted by pride—and the more you talk about them, they fluff themselves up.

00:55:32.757 --> 00:55:39.079
Why? Because that's what they're after. They want you to acknowledge them.

00:55:39.080 --> 00:55:43.634
And the more you acknowledge them—'I see a demon there! I see a demon there!'—they go, 'Oh, you do?

00:55:43.635 --> 00:55:51.358
You see me?'and they get all excited about it because it's all about pride.

00:55:51.359 --> 00:56:01.250
Do you see? And so many Christians focus on the demonic way too much. I don't talk about it very long.

00:56:01.251 --> 00:56:07.239
And the same thing about witchcraft: I take authority over it and I'll leave it alone.

00:56:07.240 --> 00:56:13.719
Hexes and vexes and all that—it's real. But they don't have power over me.

00:56:13.720 --> 00:56:19.654
A curse without a cause cannot stand. Greater is he that is in me than he that is in the world.

00:56:19.655 --> 00:56:27.479
A thousand shall fall at our side and 10,000 on our right hand, but nothing shall come nigh us. Either you believe it or you don't.

00:56:27.480 --> 00:56:35.399
And this covenant of his blood and what he did for us on that cross—I am seated with him in the heavenlies.

00:56:35.400 --> 00:56:42.854
And when you understand and you're a believing believer and you walk in the authority of the believer, nothing shall by any means hurt you.

00:56:42.855 --> 00:56:52.559
And I say to be absent from the body is to be present with the Lord. I have victory no matter what.

00:56:52.560 --> 00:57:05.352
So when I tell you I see demonic stuff, yes, but they're defeated. So why talk about something that's been defeated?

00:57:05.353 --> 00:57:11.879
And all these people talking about singing angels and talking angels—I don't believe it.

00:57:11.880 --> 00:57:16.959
Do you know? They are always on assignment to give him glory.

00:57:16.960 --> 00:57:25.399
They don't ever bring glory to themselves. Never. They always are looking to him.

00:57:25.400 --> 00:57:32.355
Every time I've had it, they always are looking to him unless they have a word to tell you.

00:57:32.356 --> 00:57:36.679
And the other night, he had an opal outfit and he stood right over here.

00:57:36.680 --> 00:57:40.392
He was on assignment. He gave me a message; he told me what he was supposed to say.

